	<annotations>
		<text id="0" type="text/plain" rect="(-967.0, 401.9642857142858, 438.0, 277.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">-- Data Overview --
the cyber security breaches dataset contains information about security breaches in the US from 1997 to 2014.

it includes various features such as the name of the covered entity, type of breach, individuals affected, and more.

-- Problem -- 
the goal is to analyze the characterisitcs of cyber security breaches, understand the relationship between the variables, and potentially predict the impact of breaches based on historical data</text>
		<text id="1" type="text/plain" rect="(-307.2380952380952, 273.25, 291.0, 138.75)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">-- from the data table widget -- 
1055 instances
7 features (12.3% missing data)
no target variable
3 meta attributes (53.6% missing data)</text>
		<text id="2" type="text/plain" rect="(-593.1666666666666, 288.52380952380963, 250.75, 89.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">-- from feature statistics --
missing data mainly comes from breach_end (910 instances)
</text>
		<text id="3" type="text/plain" rect="(-809.0357142857143, 718.9166666666666, 290.0, 180.5)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">-- data info --
name: cyber-security-breaches
size: 1055 rows, 10 columns
features: 3 categorical, 4 numberic
meta: 3 text
missing data: 910 (12.3%) in features, 5091 (160%) in meta variables</text>
		<text id="4" type="text/plain" rect="(-225.0, 653.3333333333333, 319.99999999999994, 166.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Using the distribution widget, we filter the "location of breached information" and "type of breach" to only use the features with many datas (filter out minor datas)</text>
		<text id="5" type="text/plain" rect="(101.66666666666663, 663.3333333333335, 150.0, 122.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Select "Type of breach" as target, we will predict what kind of breach will happen </text>
		<text id="6" type="text/plain" rect="(245.0, 665.0, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">impute any missing datas</text>
		<text id="7" type="text/plain" rect="(401.66666666666674, 663.3333333333333, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">preprocess with intervals (-1,1)</text>
		<text id="8" type="text/plain" rect="(570.0, 675.0000000000001, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Separate the data to 70% training and 30% sample data</text>
		<text id="9" type="text/plain" rect="(1211.666666666667, 453.3333333333335, 150.0, 298.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Predictions:

Random forest
F1 = 0.547
Prec = 0.529

SVM
F1 = 0.419
Prec = 0.489

Logistic regression
F1 = 0.386
Prec = 0.340</text>
		<text id="10" type="text/plain" rect="(778.3333333333333, 646.6666666666667, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Use SVM, Logisitic regression, and random forest as ML models</text>
		<text id="11" type="text/plain" rect="(1378.3333333333335, 541.6666666666667, 150.0, 144.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">because of the large datas in the "type of breach" is it difficult to assess the confusion matrix</text>
		<text id="12" type="text/plain" rect="(-583.3333333333334, 1286.6666666666665, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">geocoding gets the longitude and latitude of the US states</text>
		<text id="13" type="text/plain" rect="(-216.66666666666674, 1198.3333333333335, 150.0, 78.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Visualize the data breach in the US map</text>
		<text id="14" type="text/plain" rect="(-291.66666666666663, 951.6666666666665, 150.0, 122.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Using the edit domain widget, merge the datas together to make it easier to analyze</text>
		<text id="15" type="text/plain" rect="(-48.33333333333337, 1071.6666666666665, 150.0, 122.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Select "Type of breach" as target, we will predict what kind of breach will happen </text>
		<text id="16" type="text/plain" rect="(85.0, 918.3333333333333, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">impute any missing datas</text>
		<text id="17" type="text/plain" rect="(210.0, 1066.6666666666665, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">preprocess with intervals (-1,1)</text>
		<text id="18" type="text/plain" rect="(351.66666666666663, 1064.9999999999995, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Seperate the data to 70% training and 30% sample data</text>
		<text id="19" type="text/plain" rect="(565.0, 800.0, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Use SVM, Logisitic regression, and random forest as ML models</text>
		<text id="20" type="text/plain" rect="(1025.0, 880.0, 150.0, 320.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Predictions:

